Iran's loss to England was a serious blow to their chances of making it out of the group stage. In the USA-Wales game, it looked like the USA was the slightly better team.

The tie between Wales and USA and the convincing loss of Iran means this might come down to tiebreaker procedure. I suspect England will have a strong chance of winning against both USA and Wales. I suspect Iran with lose both.
Aligning a bit more with ELO odds

In the most likely scenario, USMNT competes with Iran and Wales for a single slot to get out of the group stage. There is a small chance that England falters, leaving two spots open, so I will give the USMNT an even chance of getting out of the group stage.

The US has improved greatly over the past few years with players such as Pulisic, Reyna, McKennie, and a few others. They have a talented, young, upcoming team that could always prove me wrong. However, Iran/Wales/USA are all fighting for 2nd place. England is a shoe-in already due to the sheer talent they possess, even with a bad manager. Iran is unlikely to win, especially with the internal turmoil in their country, but they are a tough game nevertheless. Wales is similar in skill to the US and it's a tight race between those 2. I have Wales getting 2nd but I would not be surprised if the US managed to make it. However, they would likely play Netherlands, Argentina, or France in the round of 16 which would be a VERY tough game.

For group stage I've gone with a baseline of 66%, assuming England progress (notwithstanding their poor recent form) that leaves one spot for the other 3 teams, difficult to decide between the three since they're from different confederations so no real comparisons.

Base rates - looking at US in past world cups, their track record is mediocre. They have participated in 10 world cups since 1930. Of those 10, they have made semi finals once (1930), quarter finals once (2002), round of 16 four times (1934, 1994, 2010, 2014), and the rest (four tournaments) they were knocked out of from the group stage.
Wales.

Loved @steven_meyers answer which gave me more color into the mechanics of the tournament. Based on ELO ratings, to get to the round of 16 they would need to get the 2nd spot again England (rated 6th at https://www.eloratings.net/) or Iran (23rd and close to home) or the 4th team (either Ukriane 16th or Wales 22rd). So basically we're asking what are the chances they can either have some amazing run and upset England or beat both of the other teams that are close to them in skill. Base rate would be close to 1 in 3 that they progress past the group stage but US soccer and a young team without much experience together tells me it is less than that, so going with 25%. Assigning 1/10th of that to progressing to the quarterfinals. Anything beyond that is well south of 1%.

Took vig-adjusted implied odds from DraftKings for Group Stage and Finals, then extrapolated back from finals using conservative estimate as to likelihood of US win at later stage in tournament. Then averaged with current crowd predictions.
The team is looking strong but US soccer is still a long way from a serious run at the World Cup

Given the playoffs involving Wales, Scotland & Ukraine are still to be played, it is early to predict. The US are likely the 3rd ranked team in the group, if the playoffs go to ranking, albeit the three unseeded teams are quite closely ranked. A group stage exit would not be a surprise, but if the US were to progress in second, likely opponents are Netherlands, or perhaps AFCON winners Senegal - both tricky games. The 'likely' 1/4 final opponent appears to be Argentina, so I will stop there.
The USA will meet England first thing, they may be able to advance to honorably meet Iran, and advance more, after that match.

Rank: Currently ranked 15th n the world. But rankings unreliable due to paucity of international matches to provide direct evidence. Rankings within continents more reliable because most internationals are against countries on same continent, but relative strength of different continents hard to pitch - North America traditionally weak.

Calculation based on a) the probability that any team will be kicked out in any given round based on the number of competing teams; and b) the relative ELO scores of the (prospective) opponents of the USA in each round, taken from https://www.eloratings.net/.
